The paper discusses differentially private learning and optimization algorithms, which are typically studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography (cs.CR) communities. The paper also introduces two algorithms that operate over discrete and continuous domains, which suggests that the paper may be relevant to the discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT) communities. Finally, the paper includes an empirical evaluation of the non-convex case, which suggests that the paper may be relevant to the statistical learning (cs.SI) community.
